NCE,Montfort-le-Rotrou":"Montfort-le-Rotrou, Sarthe, Pays de la Loire, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"PAYNEL","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Payne  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Payne","meanings":["English: from the Middle English and Old French personal name <i>Pai(e)n</i>, <i>Pagen</i> (from Latin <i>Paganus</i>), a fairly common personal name among Normans. It derived from a word that originally meant ‘villager, rustic’, later ‘heathen’, but it had doubtless lost these connotations in its use as a late medieval personal name. This name has also been established in Ireland since the 14th century.","History: Thomas Payne, who was a freeman of Plymouth Colony in 1639, was the founder of a large American family, which included Robert Treat Paine (1731–1814), one of the signers of the Declaration of Independence. See also   Paine  ."]}]},{"name":"DE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"HAMBYE","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Hanby near Welton le Marsh, in Lincolnshire, which is named from the Old Norse personal name <i>Hundi</i> + Old Norse <i>býr</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’."],"variants":[{"name":"Hanby","meanings":["English: variant of   Hamby  ."]}]},{"name":"petronille","type":"FIRST","meanings":["An old female name; an Italian diminutive formed from Pietro, i.e. Peter."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When petronille PAYNEL DE HAMBYE was born about 1200, in France, her father, Fulk II Paynel of Bampton, was 52 and her mother, Agatha du Hommet, was 50. She married Eudon de Montfort. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1190–":"umbes 1200–Surnud","1170–1256":"1170–1256","1185–1253":"1185–1253","1188–Female":"1188–Surnud","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1180–1270":"1180–1270","1225–1299":"1225–1299","1250–1291":"1250–1291","1150–1215":"1150–1215","1151–1190":"1151–1190","1190":"1190","about 1190":"umbes 1200","1253":"1253","Abt 1225":"umbes 1225","1185":"1185","1151":"1151","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","ABT 1250":"umbes 1250","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1256":"1256","1299":"1299","1200":"1200","1188":"1188","France":"Prantsusmaa","Montfort-sur-Meu, Rennes, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Montfort-sur-Meu, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Montfort-le-Gesnois,72241,Sarthe,Pays de la Loire,FRANCE,Montfort-le-Rotrou":"Montfort-le-Rotrou, Sarthe, Pays de la Loire, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1190–":"noin 1200–Kuollut","1170–1256":"1170–1256","1185–1253":"1185–1253","1188–Female":"1188–Kuollut","1190–1248":"1190–1248","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1180–1270":"1180–1270","1225–1299":"1225–1299","1250–1291":"1250–1291","1150–1215":"1150–1215","1151–1190":"1151–1190","1190":"1190","about 1190":"noin 1200","1253":"1253","Abt 1225":"noin 1225","1185":"1185","1151":"1151","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","ABT 1250":"noin 1250","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1256":"1256","1299":"1299","1200":"1200","1188":"1188","France":"Ranska","Montfort-sur-Meu, Renn